# Day 07 - Hashing

## What is Hashing?

### Definition

Hashing is a technique used to store and retrieve data efficiently by converting data into a fixed-size value using a hash function.

The generated value is called:

- Hash Value
- Hash Code
- Hash Index

Hashing helps locate data quickly without searching through all elements.

---

## Real-Life Analogy

Imagine a library containing 1000 books.

Instead of searching every shelf, a special formula assigns each book a shelf number.

Using that shelf number, the book can be found instantly.

This is similar to hashing.

---

## Advantages of Hashing

- Fast Search
- Fast Insertion
- Fast Deletion
- O(1) Average Time Complexity

---

## Common Applications

- Dictionaries
- Frequency Counters
- Caches
- Database Indexing
- Compiler Design
- Cryptography

---

